The James Hardie building materials firm which established the $1.5 billion fund in 2006, claims it is short $3.5 million for its compensation fund payouts due to the decline in the American housing market which provides 85 percent of its company sales. The settlement stipulates that in the event of a shortfall, victims will receive funds in the form of instalments
