Country music singer-songwriter icon and 1996 Country Music Hall of Fame inductee Buck Owens has passed away at his residence. He was 76
Owens was responsible for over 20 number one hits including his first, "Act Naturally," in 1963, "Together Again," and "I've Got a Tiger by the Tail". Most of his biggest hits were released from the mid 1960's to mid 1970's
Most of his biggest hits were released from the mid 1960's to mid 1970's. Among the numerous recording artists who recorded his songs were Emmylou Harris, the Beatles, who recorded "Act Naturally", and Dwight Yoakam, who had a 1988 duet with Owens on "Streets of Bakersfield
